<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-06-26T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-06-26T10:00:00-05:00" n="339" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d339">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/12522:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Bulgaria</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Earle</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sofia</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-06-26T17:00:00+02:00">June 26,
                                    1941—5 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received June 27—3:14 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>292. In a long conversation with the Foreign Minister he stated to me
                            again and again the strong desire of the King and Government to maintain
                            cordial relations with our country no matter what happens.</p>
                        <p>He impressed me with his sincerity but this in no way changes my opinion
                            that Bulgaria will do exactly what Germany orders.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Earle</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>